description: Grand Designs House of the Year: Series 3 Technology Documentary hosted by Kevin McCloud, published by Channel 4 broadcasted as part of Ch4. series in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/f/f2/Grand-Designs-House-of-the-Year-Series-3-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Grand Designs House of the Year: Series 3 Kevin McCloud visits the country's most cutting edge homes as they compete for the 2017 Royal Institute of British Architects House of the Year 4) The Minimalists and the Winner Kevin McCloud reveals the winner of the most prestigious prize for residential architecture, the Royal Institute of British Architects House of the Year 2017. But first, Kevin, the architect Damion Burrows and magazine editor Michelle Ogundehin sift the final category from the long list, all of them homes that share a pared-back, minimal look. Properties include a former caretaker's shed in London and a small but perfectly formed home with oak panelling and sleek polished concrete floors.
